# Flutter i18n Rules

## Deprecated APIs are not allowed

```dart
// BAD: static lookup does not rebuild on language change.
Text("shop_title".tr)
product.titleL10n
TranslatorGlobal.currentLang

// GOOD: reactive language read and explicit model localization.
final lang = ref.watch(appSettingsProvider).language;
Text(ref.tr("shop_title"))
product.localizedTitleFor(lang)
```

## Widget translation

- Use `ref.watch(appSettingsProvider).language` to get `AppLanguage lang`.
- Pass `lang` explicitly to `product.localizedXxxFor(lang)` methods.
- Use `ref.tr("key")` for widget UI strings.

## Async contexts

Use `ref.read`, not `ref.watch`, inside `onPressed`, `onTap`, and async methods:

```dart
final lang = ref.read(appSettingsProvider).language;
```

## Lint check

Run `dart run tool/lint_i18n.dart` before merge. It must report 0 issues.

## Adding new languages

1. Add an entry to the `AppLanguage` enum.
2. Add strings to `app_strings.dart` for zh-CN, en, and zh-TW.
3. Update language parsing in `app_settings_provider.dart`.
